HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 213
By Butler
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Aaron Summerall on
his receipt of the Governor's Volunteer Stars
Award.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those estimable citizens who have dedicated their time and energies to helping
others; and
WHEREAS, each year, 1.3 million Tennessee volunteers give over 99 million hours of
community service, contributing $2.6 billion to Tennessee's economy; and
WHEREAS, these volunteers are the backbone of our communities, and by donating
their time and talents to fulfill needs that would otherwise go unmet, they embody the spirit of
giving; and
WHEREAS, Aaron Summerall of Roane County is one such exemplary person, who is a
recipient of the Governor's Volunteer Stars Award in recognition of his laudable commitment to
his community; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Summerall has served his community through engagement in school,
civic, government, and volunteer activities; he serves as the vice president of his class, has
completed Roane County Youth Leadership, and serves as an officer on local, state, and
national levels for HOSA; and
WHEREAS, Aaron Summerall also attended Boys State and recently served as a youth
representative in the opioid drug settlement decision process for Roane County; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Summerall is a model citizen; his commitment to helping others through
volunteerism epitomizes the spirit of the Volunteer State, and he should be specially recognized;
now, therefore,
HJR0213
003549
